SIMPLE: cassock
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cassock
<hw>Cas"sock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>casaque</ets>, fr. It. <ets>casacca</ets>, perh. fr. L.
<ets>casa</ets> cottage, in It., house; or of Slavic origin.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A long outer garment formerly worn by men and women,
as well as by soldiers as part of their uniform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A garment resembling a long frock
coat worn by the clergy of certain churches when officiating, and by
others as the usually outer garment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cassocked</ent>⟦br⟧
